The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Exports to look up after August
                                                                                                               Exports to look up after August
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, May 14: The government expects exports to start picking up after August. Exports fell a massive 33 per cent in April.        
	Merchandise exports have shrunk for the seventh month in a row in April as the markets in the US and Europe are yet to recover from the recession.         
	The global slowdown has seen buyers cancelling orders for garment, handicraft and jewellery.        
	Exports are estimated to be at $10.79 billion in April. It is expected to be down 33 per cent. Imports in April were also down 32 per cent from a year earlier. The slowdown will continue till August, commerce secretary G.K. Pillai told reporters at an industry conference.        
	He said the fall in exports was expected with the global slowdown and a contraction of 9 per cent in global trade.                                                                                                                                        
